- Support added for opening file to specific line number.

pr_title: Added custom IDE and improved other IDE launch commands
pr_body:
- Resolves https://github.com/starfixdev/starfix/issues/81
- Simplifies other ide launch methods
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 687459991, 'comment_body': 'why these eclipse related checks?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 7, 31, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'maxandersen', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 687538635, 'comment_body': "That's not an eclipse related check . Its intended for URL having line numbers at the end. 

Example: https://github.com/jbangdev/jbang/blob/main/build.gradle#L12

The filePath we get will be:`jbang/blob/main/build.gradle#L12`  

Using this check we will convert it something like:
`jbang/blob/main/build.gradle:12`

I thought it'd be more meaningful (we don't know which IDE is being used but apparently this format looked more meaningful for IDEs to support) .

", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 12, 9, 19, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'fahad-israr', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692776686, 'comment_body': 'okey - really should let each IDE subclass decide how they want to treat this.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 20, 8, 43, 15, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'maxandersen', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 692776977, 'comment_body': 'but i guess for custom IDE it can make sense.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 8, 20, 8, 43, 39, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'maxandersen', 'type': 'User'}]
